    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-30T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-30T11:00:00-05:00" n="525"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d525">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.00/1788: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Finland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gullion</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Helsinki</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-30T18:00:00+02:00"
                            >March 30, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:01 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>292. Department of State memorandum on foreign policy of March 21<note n="97"
                        xml:id="d525fn97">The Department released to the press on March 21, 1944, a
                        memorandum entitled, “Bases of the Foreign Policy of the United States”; see
                        Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, March 25, 1944, p.
                        275.</note> seems not to have been reported except in few lines by FNB<note
                        n="98" xml:id="d525fn98">Finska Nyhets Byrån, Finnish News Bureau.</note>
                    from United States of America and was hardly noted in press.</p>
                <p>Procopé has referred to memorandum in his cables and there is tendency here to be
                    encouraged by references to rights of small nations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gullion</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
